So you guys did a very great

00:22:46.872 --> 00:22:49.911
job.
[APPLAUSE] All right.

00:22:49.911 --> 00:22:54.895
This works.
That's how they calculated the

00:22:54.895 --> 00:23:00.000
diameter of the nucleus.
That's it.

00:23:00.000 --> 00:23:07.003
Nothing else involved in this.
That is the principle behind

00:23:07.003 --> 00:23:10.383
how it was done.
Very simple.

00:23:10.383 --> 00:23:17.628
That is the principle behind
how the quark was discovered and

00:23:17.628 --> 00:23:21.733
the size of the quark was
revealed.

00:23:21.733 --> 00:23:27.529
That is terrific.
Now, we've got the problem that

00:23:27.529 --> 00:23:34.532
the scientific community had in
1911, 1912, right after the

00:23:34.532 --> 00:23:40.638
discovery of the nucleus.
And the problem is,

00:23:40.638 --> 00:23:45.814
now we know the atom has got a
nucleus, we know it has got an

00:23:45.814 --> 00:23:49.523
electron, what is the structure
of the atom?

00:23:49.523 --> 00:23:53.923
How does the electron and the
nucleus hang together?

00:23:53.923 --> 00:23:57.632
In particular,
what we have to do is we have

00:23:57.632 --> 00:24:02.118
to ask what is the force of
attraction that keeps the

00:24:02.118 --> 00:24:06.000
nucleus and the electron
together?

00:24:06.000 --> 00:24:11.541
We are going to talk,
here, about this classical

00:24:11.541 --> 00:24:18.026
description of the atom.
And we've got to talk about the

00:24:18.026 --> 00:24:24.746
force of the interaction first.
Well, there are four known

00:24:24.746 --> 00:24:30.406
fundamental forces.
What is the force that is the

00:24:30.406 --> 00:24:33.837
weakest force?
Gravity.

00:24:33.837 --> 00:24:38.025
Absolutely.
What is the force that is the

00:24:38.025 --> 00:24:41.794
next stronger force?
Electromagnetic.

00:24:41.794 --> 00:24:45.563
Absolutely.
What is the next stronger

00:24:45.563 --> 00:24:47.342
force?
Weak force.

00:24:47.342 --> 00:24:50.693
And the next force?
Strong force.

00:24:50.693 --> 00:24:54.880
All right.
The weak and the strong forces

00:24:54.880 --> 00:25:02.000
here, these are intranuclear
forces within the nucleus.

00:25:02.000 --> 00:25:07.192
That's what keeps the protons
and neutrons and the quarks

00:25:07.192 --> 00:25:09.695
together.
For the most part,

00:25:09.695 --> 00:25:14.516
the weak and the strong force
don't have an effect in

00:25:14.516 --> 00:25:18.596
chemistry, with the exception
for beta decay,

00:25:18.596 --> 00:25:24.158
for some radioactive elements.
That's where you need to think

00:25:24.158 --> 00:25:27.496
about, in particular,
the weak force.

00:25:27.496 --> 00:25:32.081
Gravity also --
Well, gravity actually has no

00:25:32.081 --> 00:25:36.244
known consequence for chemistry.
It doesn't mean that there

00:25:36.244 --> 00:25:40.263
isn't one, but it has no known
consequence for chemistry.

00:25:40.263 --> 00:25:44.641
All of chemistry is tied up in
this force, the electromagnetic

00:25:44.641 --> 00:25:47.296
force.
Now, what I am going to do is I

00:25:47.296 --> 00:25:51.531
am going to simplify it just a
little bit and just call this

00:25:51.531 --> 00:25:54.904
the Coulomb force.
And why I am going to do that

00:25:54.904 --> 00:26:00.000
is going to be a little more
obvious when you get to 8.02.

00:26:00.000 --> 00:26:04.576
But I am going to call it the
Coulomb interaction.

00:26:04.576 --> 00:26:09.153
And we know what the Coulomb
force law looks like.

00:26:09.153 --> 00:26:12.703
The Coulomb force law is the
following.

00:26:12.703 --> 00:26:17.280
Say I have a positive charge,
which is my nucleus.

00:26:17.280 --> 00:26:21.296
I am going to call that force
plus e.

00:26:21.296 --> 00:26:25.500
And at some distance R,
R is the distance now,

00:26:25.500 --> 00:26:30.730
between that nucleus and the
negatively charged particle,

00:26:30.730 --> 00:26:36.460
which is my electron.
I can describe the force of

00:26:36.460 --> 00:26:42.203
attraction between this electron
in the nucleus by the following

00:26:42.203 --> 00:26:46.031
expression.
That force, which is a function

00:26:46.031 --> 00:26:51.591
of the distance between the two
charges, is just the magnitude

00:26:51.591 --> 00:26:56.786
of the charge on the negatively
charged particle times the

00:26:56.786 --> 00:27:01.617
magnitude on the positively
charged particle over 4 pi

00:27:01.617 --> 00:27:07.177
epsilon nought r squared.

00:27:07.177 --> 00:27:11.517
Now, I am going to treat this

00:27:11.517 --> 00:27:15.423
force, just for simplicity
purposes right now,

00:27:15.423 --> 00:27:18.895
as a scalar.
I am not going to talk about

00:27:18.895 --> 00:27:22.454
the direction,
but because this is a force

00:27:22.454 --> 00:27:27.663
between a positive and negative
charge, this is an attractive

00:27:27.663 --> 00:27:30.701
force.
This epsilon down here is the

00:27:30.701 --> 00:27:36.116
permittivity of the vacuum.
It is in there for doing our

00:27:36.116 --> 00:27:40.197
unit conversion correctly.
That is all I will say about

00:27:40.197 --> 00:27:42.540
it.
Maybe you will talk a little

00:27:42.540 --> 00:27:45.866
bit more about it in 8.02.
And then, finally,

00:27:45.866 --> 00:27:49.569
here is the r squared.
That is the important part.

00:27:49.569 --> 00:27:53.877
That is the distance between
the electron and the nucleus.

00:27:53.877 --> 00:27:58.337
And what I want you to notice
here-- I don't need the screen

00:27:58.337 --> 00:28:00.865
down yet.
Hello.

00:28:00.865 --> 00:28:05.913
She just switched it?
Oh, all right.

00:28:05.913 --> 00:28:11.105
Sorry.
It looks like I'm not going to

00:28:11.105 --> 00:28:15.432
get to it, actually.
Thank you.

00:28:15.432 --> 00:28:24.375
What I want you to notice here
is that when r goes to infinity,

00:28:24.375 --> 00:28:30.441
what is the force going to do?
Zero.

00:28:30.441 --> 00:28:34.764
When those two particles are
infinitely far apart,

00:28:34.764 --> 00:28:40.147
you've got an infinity in the
denominator, this force is zero,

00:28:40.147 --> 00:28:43.235
there is no attraction between
them.

00:28:43.235 --> 00:28:47.470
But when r goes to zero,
what does that force do?

00:28:47.470 --> 00:28:49.588
Infinity.
When r is zero,

00:28:49.588 --> 00:28:52.411
there is an infinity large
force.

00:28:52.411 --> 00:28:56.294
And in between,
what is happening is that the

00:28:56.294 --> 00:29:03.000
closer the particles get to each
other, the larger the force.

00:29:03.000 --> 00:29:08.413
The more attraction there is.
The more they want to be even

00:29:08.413 --> 00:29:11.306
closer to each other.
All right.

00:29:11.306 --> 00:29:15.693
Now, what this equation is
telling me is simply,

00:29:15.693 --> 00:29:20.920
what is the force of attraction
between the nucleus in an

00:29:20.920 --> 00:29:25.306
electron for a fixed distance r?
In other words,

00:29:25.306 --> 00:29:30.906
if I were holding the electron
and the nucleus in my hands at

00:29:30.906 --> 00:29:34.920
some distance r,
that equation would tell me

00:29:34.920 --> 00:29:40.442
what the force was.
And you can bet that in order

00:29:40.442 --> 00:29:44.147
to keep them apart,
I would really have to be

00:29:44.147 --> 00:29:46.842
pulling like this.
You'd feel it.

00:29:46.842 --> 00:29:51.810
But you also know that if you
let them go, what would happen

00:29:51.810 --> 00:29:55.263
is that they would move toward
each other.

00:29:55.263 --> 00:30:00.147
What this equation does not
tell us is how they move toward

00:30:00.147 --> 00:30:04.600
each other.
It does not tell us how r

00:30:04.600 --> 00:30:09.281
changes with time.
It doesn't tell us anything

00:30:09.281 --> 00:30:15.627
about r as a function of time.
Although we know the force law,

00:30:15.627 --> 00:30:21.557
we don't know anything from
that force law about how those

00:30:21.557 --> 00:30:26.550
two particles move under
influence of that force.

00:30:26.550 --> 00:30:33.000
And so what we need is we need
an equation of motion.

00:30:33.000 --> 00:30:37.864
And the equation of motion that
was known at that time is,

00:30:37.864 --> 00:30:42.983
of course, Newton's equations
of motion, Newtonian mechanics,

00:30:42.983 --> 00:30:47.250
classical mechanics,
the mechanics that governs the

00:30:47.250 --> 00:30:51.688
motion of all bodies around us
that we see easily and

00:30:51.688 --> 00:30:54.589
astronomical bodies.
In particular,

00:30:54.589 --> 00:30:58.258
Newton's second law,
F equals ma,

00:30:58.258 --> 00:31:02.695
this force equals the mass of
the particles times the

00:31:02.695 --> 00:31:06.201
acceleration.
And, of course,

00:31:06.201 --> 00:31:10.608
in this acceleration term,
well, I think you know what's

00:31:10.608 --> 00:31:13.413
in there.
In that acceleration term,

00:31:13.413 --> 00:31:17.660
let me just write it out,
the acceleration then is the

00:31:17.660 --> 00:31:22.628
change in velocity with respect
to time and the velocity is the

00:31:22.628 --> 00:31:26.233
change in the position r with
respect to time.

00:31:26.233 --> 00:31:30.000
So we have a second derivative
here.

00:31:30.000 --> 00:31:36.505
What is in this force law is a
way to get r as a function of

00:31:36.505 --> 00:31:40.254
time under influence of this
force.

00:31:40.254 --> 00:31:46.429
So we take this force and we
substitute it in here and we

00:31:46.429 --> 00:31:52.273
would be able to solve a
differential equation for how

00:31:52.273 --> 00:31:59.000
those two bodies moved under
influence of that force.

00:31:59.000 --> 00:32:04.134
And when we solved this
equation, we would know exactly

00:32:04.134 --> 00:32:08.128
where the two bodies would be at
all times.

00:32:08.128 --> 00:32:13.549
As long as we know where the
bodies were when they started

00:32:13.549 --> 00:32:18.588
out, using that force law and
this equation of motion,

00:32:18.588 --> 00:32:23.723
we could tell you what r would
be for all future times.

00:32:23.723 --> 00:32:30.000
That's called deterministic.
That's classical mechanics.

00:32:30.000 --> 00:32:36.304
Well, we're not going to do it,
but we could actually set up a

00:32:36.304 --> 00:32:42.299
differential equation and solve
for what r(t) is using that

00:32:42.299 --> 00:32:45.090
force law.
We could do that.

00:32:45.090 --> 00:32:51.085
And if I did that and if I
started out the electron and the

00:32:51.085 --> 00:32:56.666
nucleus at one angstrom from
each other, like they are,

00:32:56.666 --> 00:33:01.421
roughly speaking,
in an atom, what would happen

00:33:01.421 --> 00:33:07.002
is that that electron would
plummet into the nucleus in

00:33:07.002 --> 00:33:13.718
10^-10 seconds.
If I solved these equations,

00:33:13.718 --> 00:33:21.156
I would find that r would be
equal to zero and t equal to

00:33:21.156 --> 00:33:27.000
10^-10 seconds.
We've got a problem here.

00:33:27.000 --> 00:33:30.557
The problem is that this
classical physics,

00:33:30.557 --> 00:33:35.554
Newton's second law and the
force law, it is predicting that

00:33:35.554 --> 00:33:40.213
after 10^-10 seconds the
electron and the nucleus are on

00:33:40.213 --> 00:33:44.363
top of each other,
they've neutralized each other.

00:33:44.363 --> 00:33:49.614
We no longer have an atom that
has a diameter of 10^-10 meters.

00:33:49.614 --> 00:33:52.579
That's contrary to our
observations.

00:33:52.579 --> 00:33:58.000
This is saying the atom
collapses in 10^-10 seconds.

00:33:58.000 --> 00:34:03.391
But what we see is that the
atom seemingly lives forever.

00:34:03.391 --> 00:34:08.397
So we've got a big problem
here, as they did in 1911,

00:34:08.397 --> 00:34:11.574
1912.
And the problem is that this

00:34:11.574 --> 00:34:16.677
kind of classical way of
thinking does not predict our

00:34:16.677 --> 00:34:20.624
observations.
It does not predict the fact

00:34:20.624 --> 00:34:25.052
that the atom lives together,
it lives forever.

00:34:25.052 --> 00:34:31.603
It says the atom falls apart.
So it could be that the Coulomb

00:34:31.603 --> 00:34:35.213
force law is wrong,
or it could be that this

00:34:35.213 --> 00:34:40.335
equation of motion is incorrect.
And of course what's going to

00:34:40.335 --> 00:34:45.122
turn out is that this equation
of motion does not work for

00:34:45.122 --> 00:34:48.732
electrons in atoms.
You cannot use classical

00:34:48.732 --> 00:34:52.931
mechanics to describe the
electron within the atom.

00:34:52.931 --> 00:34:57.297
We need a new kind of
mechanics, and that new kind of

00:34:57.297 --> 00:35:02.000
mechanics is going to be quantum
mechanics.

00:35:02.000 --> 00:35:05.294
That is where we will pick up
on Monday.

00:35:05.294 --> 00:35:06.627
Have a nice weekend.

